description: a structured classification for a diverse group of living organisms, spanning across several kingdoms and phyla

command.prompt:
Generate 2 new attributes for a table of a structured classification for a diverse group of living organisms, spanning across several kingdoms and phyla. The semi-colon-separated header of attributes to not generate is:
Family;Latin Name;Phylum;Class;Order;Suborder;Genus;Species;Common Name;Size

Generate real attributes. Do not generate fictional ones. Here are the semi-colon-separated rows of the table by semantic key only:
Common Name
Virginia Opossum
Black Widow
American Alligator
Earthworm
Horseshoe Crab
Small
Dogfish Shark
European Eel
Cooper's Hawk
Sharks, Rays, Skates

Generate values of real data for all existing rows of the table. Generate and output a new table, include the table header, with only the attributes Common Name, and the new attributes in the format of a semi-colon-separated .csv file. Then explain the source of the new data.
command.output_table:
Common Name;Diet;Habitat
Virginia Opossum;Omnivore;Deciduous and Pine Forests, Urban Areas
Black Widow;Carnivore;Varied, including human structures
American Alligator;Carnivore;Freshwater Swamps, Marshes, Rivers
Earthworm;Detritivore;Soil
Horseshoe Crab;Omnivore;Estuaries, Shallow Ocean Water
Small;Insectivore;Urban Areas, Forests
Dogfish Shark;Carnivore;Ocean
European Eel;Carnivore;Freshwater and Marine Water
Cooper's Hawk;Carnivore;Woodlands, Forests
Sharks, Rays, Skates;Carnivore;Ocean
command.prologue:
New attributes: Diet;Habitat

Here is the new table with real data:
command.epilogue: The data for the 'Diet' attribute is sourced from the Animal Diversity Web (ADW) maintained by the University of Michigan. The data for the 'Habitat' attribute is sourced from the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) Red List species profiles.
